              <h2>Gummy Bears!</h2>
              <ul class="firstUl">
                To make homemade gummy bears with JELLO you only need a package of JELLO and some gelatin. The easy thing
                with this recipe is that you donâ€™t need to worry about how to sweeten it. Our kids loved this version
                because JELLO is sweet. We also love how bright and colorful the JELLO versions turned out. If you have
                extra JELLO boxes lying around the house this is a perfect way to use up the box!

                <h4>Ingredients</h4>
                <li>1 package of JELLO (85g/3 oz size)</li>
                <li>1 tablespoon of gelatin</li>
                <li>1/2 cup of water</li>
                <li>gummy bear molds</li>

                <h4>Directions</h4>
                <li>Pour 1/2 cup of water into a sauce pan set on low heat</li>
                <li>Add 1 package of Jello (85 size/3 oz size)</li>
                <li>Add 1 tablespoon of gelatin</li>
                <li>Mix until all dissolved and then remove from heat</li>
                <li>Using the dropper add into your mold</li>
              </ul>
